  "title": "disjuntivefacets with nested data",
  "body": "Below is a user, I need to set a disjunctive facet on Skills.SkillName (eg where Skills.SkillName = 'SQL' OR 'Accounting')\n\n {\"FirstName\" : \"John\",\n  \"LastName\" : \"Smith\",\n  \"JobFunction\" : \"Information Technology\",\n  \"Skills\" : [{\n      \"SkillID\" : \"2vRdiqCOE2XBDS3nsS1LA\",\n      \"SkillName\" : \"SQL\",\n      \"SkillRating\" : 3\n    }, {\n      \"SkillID\" : \"WEPMtg3JkU2xlpmgmvkYQ\",\n      \"SkillName\" : \"Accounting\",\n      \"SkillRating\" : 4\n    }, {\n      \"SkillID\" : \"d9c514035a554a5d8d99c411e43b683d\",\n      \"SkillName\" : \"Leadership\",\n      \"SkillRating\" : 4\n    }]}\n\nIve attempted a lot of different things, but here is what I think makes sense:\n\n`var preselectedCategories = ['SQL', 'Accounting'];\nvar search = instantsearch({\n    appId: 'appid',\n    apiKey: 'api',\n    indexName: 'UserActivity',\n    searchParameters: {\n        disjunctiveFacetsRefinements: {\n            Skills: {\n                SkillName: preselectedCategories\n            }\n        }\n    }\n});`\n\nDocumentation is definitely lacking on this so any help will be greatly appreciated. Thanks!\n",
